Objective Deploy a Cloud Function triggered by a Pub/Sub topic, publish a message, and verify the function fired via logs.
________________________________________
Key Concepts
•	Pub/Sub = message bus: Publisher sends to Topic → Subscriber receives
•	Messages held in topic until consumed or expired (default 7 days)
•	--trigger-topic replaces --trigger-http for event-driven functions
•	No --no-allow-unauthenticated needed — Pub/Sub uses GCP's internal event system
•	Eventarc is the service that handles event routing for 2nd Gen triggers — enabled automatically
•	base64.b64decode — Pub/Sub wraps messages in base64 for safe transport; function unwraps it
•	print() in function code writes to Cloud Logging — use gcloud functions logs read to verify
•	Pub/Sub trigger SA needs run.invoker on the underlying Cloud Run service
•	--run-service-account flag explicitly sets the invoker SA for the underlying Cloud Run service
•	Ingress blocks before IAM — Cloud Shell is outside VPC, ingress=internal blocks it at network layer
